After two years off, Glastonbury Festival 2022 finally kicks off tomorrow, with fans eagerly awaiting their chance to get to Worthy Farm for the first time since the pandemic began. With a host of huge names set to perform across five days, the Glasto’s return is set to be huge – even if transport strikes do threaten to throw a spanner in the works. Music fans will be treated to headline sets from he likes of Billie Eilish and Kendrick Lamar, as well as more than 3,000 performers across multiple stages. There’s something for everyone, but when does the event take place, and who is set to perform? Here’s everything you need to know about Glastonbury 2022: Billie Eilish plays the Pyramid Stage – the youngest solo artist to have achieved this feat so far. On the other end of the age spectrum, Sir Paul McCartney is the oldest-ever headliner. Kendrick Lamar and Diana Ross will also turn things upside down, inside out, and round and round as headliners. Fans can see full set times and plan their weekend on the Glastonbury Festival website. MORE : Glastonbury Festival set for warm sunshine – but there could also be rain MORE : Glastonbury Festival train table – will your journey be affected by rail strikes Follow Metro across our social channels, on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram Share your views in the comments below 